snippet: Green Bay (7-3) leads the N.F.L. in points scored, courtesy of 276 points over the last seven games, and Aaron Rodgers is a leading candidate for most valuable player.
abstract: Analysis; Green Bay Packers quarterback Aaron Rodgers has hit his stride after slow start to season, leading team to tie for first place in NFC North; Packers also lead NFL in points scored, and Rodgers is leading candidate for most valuable player.
lead_paragraph: Green Bay (7-3) leads the N.F.L. in points scored, courtesy of 276 points over the last seven games, and Aaron Rodgers is a leading candidate for most valuable player.

headline.main: After a Slow Start, the Rodgers Show Hits Its Stride
